FBIS3-38915 "drweu027_p_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 GREECE Leaders Comment on EU Communique on Bosnia Spokesman: Does Not Contradict Policy NC0802140094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1230 GMT 8 Feb 94 NC0802140094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Asked how he explains the government's double talk on Bosnia-Herzegovina, government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said the communique issued by the European Union [EU] Council of Ministers, which conferred in Brussels yesterday, does not contradict Greek positions. He said the firm Greek view--not just the government's--that Balkan countries should not get involved in any war remains firm. He added that Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias' handling of things was calm and responsible. [passage omitted] Asked whether the Greek presidency contacted the Serb leadership immediately after the EU foreign ministers communique was issued, Venizelos said Greece has the capability to contact and pressure all sides for a solution. He added: This capability is not limited to Serbia.
